'''Aleksey (Mihaylovich) Kryukov''' ({{lang-rus|Алексей Михайлович Крюков}}) is a Russian historian, teaching Latin and Ancient Greek at the [[Moscow State University]]. His greater field of study is Byzantine philosophy. Besides that he is known as the creator of several [[TrueType]] typefaces, resembling historical styles for the Greek, Cyrillic and Latin alphabets, among them [[Theano Didot]], a revival of the [[Didot (typeface)|Didot]] typeface of [[Firmin Didot]].
