The '''China Historical Geographic Information System''' (CHGIS) is a [[Historical GIS]] project for creating a database of populated places and historical administrative units for the period of [[History of China|Chinese history]] between 222 BCE and 1911 CE. The project creates a dataset which track changes in place names, administrative status, and geography. It is a joint project of [[Harvard University]] and [[Fudan University]]. Its director is Professor [[Peter K. Bol]] of Harvard.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fairbank.fas.harvard.edu/profiles/peter-k-bol/ |title=PETER K. BOL |publisher=Harvard University |accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author1=[[Peter Bol]] |author2=[[Jianxiong Ge]] |url=https://ejournals.unm.edu/index.php/historicalgeography/article/viewFile/2939/2418 |title=China Historical GIS |journal=Historical Geography |year=2005}}</ref>
