{{infobox Organization |name = Institute for Information on the Crimes of Communism |image = |size = |motto = |formation = 2008 |type = [[Human rights]] organization |location = [[Stockholm]] |leader_title = Chair |leader_name = Camilla Andersson |key_people = [[Carl Bildt]], [[Kristian Gerner]], [[Walburga Habsburg Douglas]], [[Mart Laar]], [[Sandra Kalniete]], [[Gunnar Hökmark]], [[Robert Conquest]], [[Stefan Hedlund]], [[Staffan Skott]] |affiliations = [[Platform of European Memory and Conscience]] |website = [http://www.upplysningomkommunismen.se upplysningomkommunismen.se] {{dead|date=November 2018}} }}
The '''Institute for Information on the Crimes of Communism''' ('''IICC''') ({{lang-sv|Upplysning om kommunismen}}, ''UOK'') is a [[Sweden]]-based [[Non-profit organization|non-profit]] and [[Non-governmental organization|non-governmental]] [[human rights]] organization, founded in 2008, with the stated purpose of "spreading essential information on the [[Criticisms of Communist party rule|crimes of communism]] and to promote vigilance against all [[Totalitarianism|totalitarian]] ideologies and antidemocratic movements".<ref>{{cite web |author= |title=UOK - Upplysning om kommunismen |url=http://www.upplysningomkommunismen.se/ |publisher=Institute for Information on the Crimes of Communism |date= |accessdate=2009-10-19}}</ref> The institute is a member organisation of the [[Platform of European Memory and Conscience]], an educational project of the [[European Union]] bringing together government institutions and NGOs active in research, documentation, awareness raising and education about the crimes of totalitarian regimes.<ref name="Platform">{{cite web|url=http://www.memoryandconscience.eu/2011/10/20/czech-prime-minister-petr-necas-the-years-of-totalitarianism-were-years-of-struggle-for-liberty/|title= Czech Prime minister Petr Nečas: The years of totalitarianism were years of struggle for liberty|last=|first=I.|date=14 October 2011|publisher=[[Platform of European Memory and Conscience]]|accessdate=14 October 2011}}</ref>
The IICC publishes information materials and media, surveys, reports, and teaching materials, participates in the public debate, and organizes film screenings, seminars, hearings, media events and exhibitions related to the subject.<ref name=about>{{cite web |author= |title=UOK - Upplysning om kommunismen |url=http://www.upplysningomkommunismen.se/?page=english |publisher=Institute for Information on the Crimes of Communism |date= |accessdate=2009-10-19}}</ref> The IICC cooperates with national institutions, embassies, institutes, NGO:s and organizations in [[Europe]], the [[United States]] and [[Canada]].<ref name=about/>
The board of directors consists of Camilla Andersson (chair), Anders Hjemdahl, Professor [[Kristian Gerner]], [[Walburga Habsburg Douglas]] MP, and Mae Liz Orrego Wennick. The institute is largely funded by the [[Confederation of Swedish Enterprise]]. The institute received the [[Templeton Freedom Awards|Templeton Freedom Award]] in 2009.
Notable honorable members of the IICC and contributors in its publications and activities are current Minister for Foreign Affairs and former Prime Minister of Sweden [[Carl Bildt]], former Prime Minister of Estonia [[Mart Laar]], former Ambassador and EU Commissioner of Latvia [[Sandra Kalniete]], Member of the European Parliament [[Gunnar Hökmark]], professor [[Robert Conquest]], professor of history [[Kristian Gerner]], professor of East European studies [[Stefan Hedlund]], professor of history [[Klas-Göran Karlsson]], author and journalist [[Staffan Skott]], author and journalist {{Interlanguage link multi|Kaa Eneberg|sv}}, and many others.<ref name=about/>
In cooperation with the [[government of Sweden]], the organisation has carried out remembrance ceremonies on the [[European Day of Remembrance for Victims of Stalinism and Nazism]]. Prime Minister [[Fredrik Reinfeldt]], Minister of Education [[Jan Björklund]] and EU Ministers [[Cecilia Malmström]] and [[Birgitta Ohlsson]] have taken part in events hosted by the institute.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.victimsofcommunism.org/media/article.php?article=6180 |title=Swedish Government honors victims of Communism and Nazism at August 23 Day Of Remembrance |author= |date=August 30, 2010 |work= |publisher=[[Victims of Communism Memorial Foundation]] |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5yf4oznUU?url=http://www.victimsofcommunism.org/media/article.php?article=6180 |archivedate=May 13, 2011 |accessdate=2011-05-10 |quote= |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.upplysningomkommunismen.se/?page=black_ribbon_day_english |title=Swedish Minister of Education, Mr. Jan Björklund inaugurates the August 23 international Day Of Remembrance for the victims of Communism and National Socialism |author= |date= |work= |publisher=Institute for Information on the Crimes of Communism |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5yfWZUI6A?url=http://www.upplysningomkommunismen.se/?page=black_ribbon_day_english |archivedate=2011-05-14 |accessdate=2011-05-14 |quote= |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>
The IICC has been involved in raising awareness about the [[Prague Declaration on European Conscience and Communism]] in Sweden and internationally.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.upplysningomkommunismen.se/?page=european-conscience|title=UOK - Upplysning om kommunismen|work=upplysningomkommunismen.se}}</ref>
