[[File:Muzej Zagreba 15.3.2016.JPG|thumb|Zagreb City Museum]]
[[File:U muzeju hrvatskoga glavnog grada.JPG|thumb|Museum]]
'''Zagreb City Museum''' or '''Museum of the City of Zagreb''' ({{lang-hr|Muzej grada Zagreba}}) located in 20 Opatička Street, was established in 1907 by the Association of the [[Brethren of the Croatian Dragon]] ({{lang-hr|Braća hrvatskoga zmaja}}). 

It is located in a restored monumental complex (12th-century Popov toranj, the [[Zagreb Observatory|Observatory]], 17th-century Zakmardi Granary) of the former Convent of the [[Poor Clares]], of 1650.<ref name=zageb_citymus>{{cite web|url=http://www.zagreb-touristinfo.hr/?id=94&l=e&nav=nav5&solo=272|title=Museum of the City of Zagreb|accessdate=2010-05-06}}</ref> 

The Museum deals with topics from the cultural, artistic, economic and [[political history]] of the city spanning from the prehistory, Roman finds to the [[modern history|modern period]]. The holdings comprise 75,000 items arranged systematically in a combined chronological and thematic approach into collections of artistic and mundane objects characteristic of the city and its history. It consists of a number paintings, maps, city views, furniture, flags, military uniforms and coats of arms.

